frameDefinitions: A Cognizer has a piece of Content in their model of the world.
These words refer to separating a Whole into Parts, or separating one part from another.
The frame concerns the vehicles that human beings use for the purpose of transportation.
Some Content is part of the mental model of a Cognizer.
An Entity is evaluated for whether or not it belongs to a particular Reference_category in a context where its category membership is doubtful.
A Reported_fact is presented by the speaker as deriving from statements (made directly to them or to others) of third parties.
frameExamples: Your boss is <t>aware</t> of your commitment.
I <t>divided</t> the class into groups in alphabetical order .
I drove a <t>limo</t> to the school dance.

It can be hard to get your money back after discovering you've bought a <t>bogus</t>
autograph for hundreds or thousands of dollars!

listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the person whose awareness of phenomena is at question. With a target verb or adjective the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is generally expressed as an External Argument with the <fen>Content</fen> expressed as an Object or Complement.
The <fen>Content</fen> is the object of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s awareness. <fen>Content</fen> can be expressed as a direct object or in a PP Complement.
Some verbs in this frame allow a <fen>Topic</fen> to be expressed in about-PPs.
<fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part that reveals the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s state to the observer.
The time interval during which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is aware of the <fen>Content</fen>.
The <fen>Whole</fen> is a single entity or an aggregate of entities which is separated into <fen>Parts</fen>.  It is usually the NP Object of a target verb.
This refers collectively to the Parts resulting from separation of a Whole:
Part-1 is the first of two Parts mentioned. This is most often the Object of a verb.
<fen>Part_2</fen> is the second of two <fen>Parts</fen> mentioned. This is usually a PP Complement. First,
With causative uses of these verbs, an Agent separates or divides something.  The Agent is usually expressed as the External Argument:
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-agent that brings about the separation.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the separation occurs.
Where the separation occurs.
Vehicle is the transportation device that the human beings use to travel.This role is incorporated into each LU in this frame.
The fact or idea which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is aware of.
The category whose applicability to the <fen>Content</fen> is known.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has awareness (or lack thereof) of the <fen>Content</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> that is being evaluated in terms of whether it is an instance of the <fen>Reference_category</fen>.
The type relative to which the <fen>Entity</fen> is evaluated.
An assertion of a state, event, property or existence or the assignment to a category that the speaker attributes to unnamed others.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Reported_fact</fen> was reported.
